CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1962, pg. 1 reads:"President Kennedy Stumps Area for Democrats - Pitt Field House was jammed with more that 8,000 of the party faithful at the Friday night rally where the Democratic party chief, President Kennedy, roasted the Republicans."
TitMainTitle: President Kennedy in Pittsburgh: Crowd with placards reading "Plum for McCann" and "Plum borough for Cooke," and "Plum for Blatt", in University of Pittsburgh field house
